               <p>Q. What is the prisoner - A. A <rs id="t18120701-106-deflabel630" type="occupation">coal-porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120701-106-defend870 t18120701-106-deflabel630"></join>. On the 22d of May, the prisoner came into my room, and emptied my master's bag of work out, and took the shoes. From the description of my landlady, I pursued him and took him, about an hundred yards from the place. He had this cup and saucer, and a bit of bees-wax, my own property, and a pair of gloves that I wore all the winter. They were taken out of my cupboard.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The prosecutor owes me for a bushel and a half of coals that I carried to him.</p>
               <p>
